cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.SY, cs.IT, cs.DS 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the challenge of latency in mobile networks and proposes a solution for sending periodic messages without collisions. 
- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) is also likely as the paper discusses the trend of centralizing processing units in distant data centers. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper proposes a deterministic scheme for sending messages, which can be seen as a control problem. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is relevant as the paper deals with the challenge of meeting protocol time constraints. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper proposes several algorithms for computing deterministic sending schemes.
